HEADWORD: Misvalue
<hw>Mis*val"ue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To value wrongly
or too little; to undervalue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But for I am so young, I dread my work⟦br⟧
Wot be <qex>misvalued</qex> both of old and young.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misvouch</ent>⟦br⟧
